


Examples on the usage of minilib.


Contents


compile_hello.sh	
	show, howto generate a configuration file for hello.c,
	and compile it using minimake


hello-tiny.conf	
	A configuration file, minimizing "hello" as far as
	currently possible with minilib.
	In favor of size all section and program headers are stripped of the elf binary.
	Per default on Linux, the elf loader sets the stack executable bit, when the
	program header is missing.
	What isn't a problem here, first hand there is no user input which could 
	result in a stackoverflow.
	However, use the ldscript onlytext_tiny with care.





